{center}
{subhead}MEDIATOR PCI busboard for Amiga 1200{def}
{left}
{p} {p}
Elbox Computer is proud to announce the new exciting product:
 MEDIATOR - PCI busboard for Amiga 1200
{p} {p}
MEDIATOR features:
{p} {p}
* PCI busboard for Amiga 1200 in: E-BOX (Winner Tower, Power Tower) and Infinitiv tower cases{p}
* 4 PCI slots - PCI 2.1 compatible{p}
* Transfer rates between PCI cards up to 132 MB/s{p}
* Transfer rates between A1200 motherboard and PCI cards up to two times faster than between A4000 and ZORRO III cards{p}
* Ready to run with existing Amiga 68k and PPC accelerator cards{p}
* Two available hardware versions:{p}
  for A1200T (MEDIATOR PCI 1200){p}
  for A1200T with ZORRO IV busboard (MEDIATOR PCI ZIV)
{p} {p}
PCI - Amiga bridge is a  PCI 2.1 compliant implementation for
connecting PCI devices, thus allowing expansion of Amiga with
all kinds of industry standard hardware products.
{p} {p}
Elbox Computer will also be offering some cost-effective PCI
add-on modules:
{p} {p}
* Graphic cards based on processors:{p}
        S3 Virge 8MB{p}
        3dfx Voodoo 3 16MB{p}
        3dfx Voodoo 5 32MB{p}
* MPEG-2 hardware decoder based on EM8400 processor{p}
* Ethernet card 100Mb/s{p}
* Sound card based on Yamaha 744 processor{p}
* USB Controller
{p} {p}
For the add-on modules, Elbox Computer will provide the necessary
software tools and drivers.
{p} {p}
MEDIATOR PCI ZIV will be available from Power Computing
and Vesalia Computer beginning with mid-July 2000.
{p} {p}
MEDIATOR PCI 1200 will be available beginning with August 2000.
{p} {p}
